    "intro": "Acts 15 unfolds in five argumentative movements: the crisis arrives at Antioch (vv. 1-5), the council deliberates (vv. 6-21), the decree is issued (vv. 22-29), the decree is received (vv. 30-35), and the second missionary journey begins amid sharp disagreement (vv. 36-41). Each movement carries the doctrinal and ecclesial freight of the chapter as a whole.",
